description: This file defines an Intent class called PopRouteIntent for handling route pop actions in a Flutter mobile app. It signals the intent to pop the current route, typically triggered by BACK or ESC actions.

classes.name: PopRouteIntent
classes.description: A class extending Intent that signals the need to pop the current route, used for navigation control in Flutter applications.
